1:
A much-beloved starter weapon
for the Palico crowd. Doubles as
a handy trowel for use in the
garden!
3:
Made from easy-to-come-by bone,
this hammer is lightweight yet
sturdy.
5:
A large sword made by smelting
down fine ore and hammering it
for three days straight.
Certified lethal.
7:
A Great Jagras weapon.
It looks like a gun but can't
shoot. Made exclusively for
bonking.
9:
Made from Kulu-Ya-Ku parts,
each note plucked from its
strings drips with sweet
nostalgia.
11:
Made from Pukei-Pukei parts.
Despite a whimsical design it
doesn't actually fire arrows.
Bonking only.
13:
Made with only the hardest
Barroth parts, this weapon is
capable of smashing boulders
into gravel.
15:
Made from Jyuratodus parts. The
strength of ancient swordsmen
seeps into the wielder's paw
pads.
17:
Made from Tobi-Kadachi parts.
It may look like an adorable
Felyne, but the ears are long
and sharp.
19:
Made from Anjanath parts. It was
made by lashing together huge
bones. This hammer hits hard
and heavy.
21:
Made from Paolumu parts.
The Felyne paw motif is cute,
but those pads are brutally
hard.
23:
Made from Rathian parts. The
strength of a queen slumbers in
this gorgeous emerald sword.
25:
Made from Radobaan parts. It's
an engineering marvel, made
using the very latest in
crafting technology.
27:
This paralyzing weapon
glows in the dark thanks to
the swarm of thunderbugs
living in the bud.
29:
Made from Legiana parts.
This azure blade is capable of
splitting glaciers.
31:
Made from Odogaron parts. A
cruel sickle meets heavy-
weighted chain in this hellish
creation.
33:
Made from Rathalos parts.
Blazing wyvern breath spews
forth with every slash of this
blade.
35:
Made from Diablos parts, this
hammer rages at prey. It's said
to be host to a bloodthirst all
of its own.
37:
Made from Kirin parts, this
weapon is modified for Palico
use. Thunder echoes with each
and every thrust.
39:
A fearsome scythe that cleaves
away consciousness. Even the
largest prey fall instantly into
restful slumber.
50:
Made from Zorah Magdaros parts.
Those who chuckle at its cute
doll form will at least go out
laughing.
62:
A Lavasioth weapon.
Made of ultra-hard materials
tempered in lava.
64:
Made from Uragaan parts.
It's capable of splintering
iron. May be the heaviest
Palico weapon ever.
66:
Made from Bazelgeuse parts.
Let the frenzy of the hunt
take you. Embrace your raw,
primal instincts.
69:
A wild Gajalaka weapon made from ore.
Sharp, and brilliant in its own right.
71:
Made from Nergigante parts.
As terrifying in function as it
is in form, it promises raw
destruction.
73:
Made from Vaal Hazak parts.
The skull whispers eerily,
"Strip every fishy morsel from
the bone."
75:
Made from Teostra parts, this
staff is the very definition of
regal. All Felynes bend the
knee to it.
77:
Made from Kushala Daora parts.
Any caught within its gale are
swept away, helpless in the
wind.
79:
Made from Xeno'jiiva parts.
Flowers adorn this sword, like
a bouquet at an underworld
wedding.
84:
A weapon used by the Lynians of the
New World. Also used as a tool in a
variety of different situations.
86:
A magic staff made of monster bone.
Grants fighting spirit to even the
most craven of cowards.
91:
The golden scales of Kulve Taroth
have been reworked to forge this
elegant, yet useful fan.
93:
A blunt Deviljho weapon that bleeds
with the same rage and green of the
monster from which it was created.
95:
A parasol created from Lunastra
parts that exudes nobility. An
elegant match for parkgoers.
97:
A replica of the infamous Mega
Buster. Square off against any
fearsome monster in 8-bit glory!
101:
A fancy weapon that glimmers with
a blue sheen. Given to a Palico
that will help usher in a new era.
103:
A shiny gold chocobo weapon for
your Palico. Wielded by the one
known as Good King Moggle Mog XII.
105:
A blade with a hilt in the shape of
a paw. Popular among Palicoes,
it's cute and dignified all at once.
107:
Requires a Spring Blossom Ticket
to craft. Inspired by dancing spring
bees, it livens up any banquet.
109:
Requires a Summer Twilight Ticket
to craft. For bonking monsters only.
No mewnlight serenades.
111:
Requires an Autumn Harvest Ticket
to craft. A weapon that'll let your
Palico enjoy trick or treating.
113:
Requires a Winter Star Ticket to
craft. Jingle some bells of your
own with this weapon!
115:
Requires an Appreciation Ticket
to craft. Get your groove on and
shine during the Appreciation Fest!
122:
An essential weapon for Palicoes
venturing into cold regions.
Shaped like a Kulu-Ya-Ku.
131:
This Beotodus weapon packs much
more punch than you'd think.
Handy for traversing snow, too!
134:
Rumor has it this sweet little
stuffed toy is among the deadliest
creations of all time.
142:
A knife made from Barioth
tusk that can freeze
prey with a single slash.
150:
A strange weapon with a long past.
Stalk your prey from the darkness,
like a true Nargacuga.
152:
A dual-edged blade made of
polished Glavenus parts.
Cauterizes when it cuts.
154:
This Brachydios weapon has
a glove at the end to punch
a hole in your unfortunate prey.
156:
One hit of this Tigrex weapon is
enough to bite into your prey's
flesh and crush its bones.
158:
This azure blade made from the
noble Shrieking Legiana is WAY
too cool not to show off.
160:
A disc-shaped weapon made from
a mysterious mined metal.
Slices its target into pieces.
163:
Boaboa weapon. Creating
this weapon with the bones of
your prey is a rite of passage.
165:
This Velkhana icicle spear will
continue piercing its enemies
as long as your Palico's spirit
remains intact.
167:
Awaken your Palico's primal lust
for battle with this Seething
Bazelgeuse weapon.
169:
This Blackveil Vaal Hazak scepter
contains a ruby that shines with
the wielder's own life force.
171:
A Namielle Palico weapon vibrant
in color, yet able to handily
smash boulders into dust.
176:
Despite its elegant look, this
Shara Ishvalda weapon strikes with
the force of a meteor impact.
178:
Claw away your prey's will to
fight with this exceptionally
sharp Ruiner Nergigante weapon.
180:
The spikes on this weapon are
bits of bone that grew through
a Savage Deviljho's skin.
182:
A Palico weapon radiating a
deep respect for the Huntsman.
Very sharp, despite its size.
184:
A Yian Garuga feather fan.
Its eerie power summons great
gales. Or was it tall tales?
186:
Each swing of this Zinogre weapon
rends the skies, summoning fierce
lightning bolts.
189:
The tip of this Rajang weapon
is adorned with a golden lion
doll that serves as a talisman.
190: F Grand God's Peer Staff α+
191:
A Furious Rajang staff that can
expand and contract at will if
the wielder is experienced enough.
193:
Go into the ring with this
Raging Brachydios weapon and
you're sure to K.O. your prey!
195:
Awakened from its slumber in the
ravine, this red Safi'jiiva spear
brings nothing but demise.
197:
A crooked scythe used by an
ancient knight in his battle
against the gods.
217:
A superbly bound tome given only
to Guild members. Reinforced to
withstand extreme circumstances.
219:
Requires a Full Bloom Ticket to
craft. Each swing sends rose
petals dancing into the air.
221:
Requires a Sizzling Spice Ticket
to craft. Let loose and cheer on
your favorite meowsters!
225:
Requires a Joyful Ticket to craft.
Shishi-mai, bring only the fortune
of the Holiday Joy! Evil, begone!
227:
Requires a Gratitude Ticket to
craft. T1m3 T0 pArTy w1tH 0uR
sPArKl1ng Fr13nDs!
239:
A diligently sharpened piece of
coral. Special care is required to
ensure its vivid color.
242:
A Frostfang Barioth saber
that pierces targets with
a cold cruelty.
248:
A weapon steeped in the aura of
a maestro. Only those willing to
lead can control the masses.
250:
A sharp, traditional weapon used widely
by the Felynes. The tip features sturdy
bone.
